PRONOTUM. Nearly as wide as head, nearly as long as wide. Elytra conjointly about 1.6 times as wide as pronotum, about 3.1 times as long as wide. Abdominal ventrite VII widely emarginate on each side of terminal margin, forming subtriangular lateral lobes, median lobe considerably developed and triangularly concave in middle (
Fig. 6E
).

FEMALE GENITALIA (
Fig. 6F
). Vagina rounded, abruptly extended apically as a long and thick duct; diverticulum and spermathecal duct arising from apex of long duct of vagina; diverticulum moderately thin and spiral, longer than spermathecal duct; spermatheca provided with thin spiral tube, tube nearly as long as diverticulum; accessory gland thin, shorter than spermatheca.
